        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3453375045" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18150069365142908706">&quot;The Idiot&quot; by Fyodor Dostoevsky is the best novel ever written. &quot;Life is a Dream&quot; by Pedro Calderon de la Barca is the best play ever written. Those two + Crime and Punishment are the only works of literature with no flaws I have read to the day.<br/><br/>Re-read: I haven&apos;t changed my opinion the slightest bit. &quot;The Idiot&quot; and &quot;Life is a Dream&quot; are perfect, with &quot;Crime and Punishment&quot;, and &quot;Don Quixote&quot; coming close.</span>
  <span id="freeText18150069365142908706" style="display:none">"The Idiot" by Fyodor Dostoevsky is the best novel ever written. "Life is a Dream" by Pedro Calderon de la Barca is the best play ever written. Those two + Crime and Punishment are the only works of literature with no flaws I have read to the day.<br /><br />Re-read: I haven't changed my opinion the slightest bit. "The Idiot" and "Life is a Dream" are perfect, with "Crime and Punishment", and "Don Quixote" coming close.</span>
