<span id="freeTextContainer1831119785114791363">A metaphysical play with hints of Chuang Tsu&apos;s butterfly dream. This beautiful Spanish classic questions fate&apos;s role in our lives. <br/><br/>Basilio, king of Poland, has his would-be parricidal son imprisoned for life. His Laius-like effort to thwart fate actually creates the situation he wants to avoid. For his part Segismund, the son, learns a valuable lesson while in prison and has a monumental decision to make. Who he is, or is to become, is at stake - does he embrace fate or does free will come in to</span>
  <span id="freeText1831119785114791363" style="display:none">A metaphysical play with hints of Chuang Tsu's butterfly dream. This beautiful Spanish classic questions fate's role in our lives. <br /><br />Basilio, king of Poland, has his would-be parricidal son imprisoned for life. His Laius-like effort to thwart fate actually creates the situation he wants to avoid. For his part Segismund, the son, learns a valuable lesson while in prison and has a monumental decision to make. Who he is, or is to become, is at stake - does he embrace fate or does free will come in to play?<br /></span>
