<div id="review_4333121064" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4333121064" />
    <a title="Forrest Price" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/59052317-forrest-price"><img alt="Forrest Price" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1605591836p2/59052317.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4333121064?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Forrest Price" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Forrest Price" href="/user/show/59052317-forrest-price">Forrest Price</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780143104827" href="/book/show/42213.Life_Is_a_Dream">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4333121064" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12645728023467008883">This play is definitely worth its classic status. While a bit archaic in its language, it was beautifully descriptive and utilized a bunch of interesting metaphors. It was a dramatic and fun to read story, and I enjoyed finding out about all the connections and relationships between the characters. I recommend this one if you&apos;re looking for a short and fun classic that still has thought-provoking themes.</span>
  <span id="freeText12645728023467008883" style="display:none">This play is definitely worth its classic status. While a bit archaic in its language, it was beautifully descriptive and utilized a bunch of interesting metaphors. It was a dramatic and fun to read story, and I enjoyed finding out about all the connections and relationships between the characters. I recommend this one if you're looking for a short and fun classic that still has thought-provoking themes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12645728023467008883" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


